Here is how to implement a debounce function in vanilla JavaScript and apply it to your search input. 

### 1. The Debounce Utility Function
A debounce function works by resetting a timer every time it is called. The target function only executes once the timer completes without being interrupted by a new keystroke.

```javascript
function debounce(func, delay) {
  let timeoutId;

  return function (...args) {
    // Clear the previous timer on every new keystroke
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);

    // Set a new timer
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => {
      func.apply(this, args);
    }, delay);
  };
}
```

