When dealing with search inputs, **debouncing alone isn't always enough**. If a user types "A" (triggers request 1), pauses, and then types "AB" (triggers request 2), Request 1 might take longer to resolve and overwrite the correct "AB" results on the screen.

You can fix this by combining your debounce with an **`AbortController`** to cancel outdated API requests:

